parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger airbag light is on
the airbag system is defective
the front passenger seat occupant detection mat sensor fails
and the airbags do not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the power steering pump makes a loud whining noise
the power steering fluid leaks
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn suddenly
the power steering fails intermittently
the vehicle is hard to steer
especially at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jerk forward, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips in and out of gear
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when accelerating
the transmission makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls
and the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jerk forward, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
and the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.
